==English==

===Etymology===
*[[cannibal]] + [[-ise]]

===Alternative spellings===
*[[cannibalize]] (''especially US'')

===Transitive verb===
'''to cannibalise''' ('''cannabilising''', '''cannabilised''', '''cannabilised''')
#To eat the flesh of (a [[human being]]).
#To remove parts of (a machine, etc) for use in other similar machines.

====Quotations====
(''remove parts of''):
*'''1991''' - When the attack ceased they managed to cannibalize parts to get one truck going and set off for the rendezvous with Fraser, only to find nobody there. &mdash; ''The SAS at War 1941–1945'', Kemp, Anthony, John Murray (Publishers) Ltd

